00:58:29.209 --> 00:58:31.090
What time do you need
to be at work?


246
00:58:31.169 --> 00:58:34.370
I have to go soon.
Can you feed Senechka?


247
00:58:34.769 --> 00:58:37.850
Of course. Get ready my love.

248
00:58:38.169 --> 00:58:42.689
Tell Vera we haven't got the meat yet,
I'll give her a call when we do.


249
00:58:43.209 --> 00:58:46.010
I woke up last night and couldn't get
back to sleep.


250
00:58:47.809 --> 00:58:49.249
I don't know.

251
00:58:50.970 --> 00:58:54.050
Don't think about it.
They will be back tonight.


252
00:58:54.970 --> 00:58:56.809
Go get ready.

253
00:59:41.649 --> 00:59:43.169
Anna, what's wrong?

254
00:59:43.649 --> 00:59:46.289
- Are you Ok?
- I don't know, Vera.


255
00:59:47.090 --> 00:59:49.609
Is it because of Dima?
Don't worry.


256
00:59:52.930 --> 00:59:56.609
I just can't anymore,
he keeps thinking about her.


257
00:59:57.450 --> 00:59:59.890
- I'm so tired of it.
- Stop it.


258
00:59:59.970 --> 01:00:03.010
My husband was cheating on me with
Tomka, I beat her up and he stopped.


259
01:00:03.090 --> 01:00:08.850
- I don't know what to do.
- Nothing! It can happen to anyone.


260
01:00:09.249 --> 01:00:14.209
- Who is she?
- If I only knew.


261
01:00:14.289 --> 01:00:17.930
You have to calm down, don't cry.

262
01:00:18.930 --> 01:00:22.450
He only loves you.
I know that for sure.


263
01:00:22.530 --> 01:00:25.890
Let's go, calm down.
Everything will be fine.


264
01:00:36.249 --> 01:00:39.090
My dear, finally you're back.

265
01:00:42.050 --> 01:00:44.010
I've missed you so much.

266
01:00:44.850 --> 01:00:46.769
- How is grandma?
- Where is Sasha?


267
01:00:47.249 --> 01:00:51.609
Grandma is fine. Her health
has been good. She said hi.


268
01:00:52.090 --> 01:00:53.570
Thank God!

269
01:00:53.649 --> 01:00:55.890
- Where is Sasha?
- Sasha?


270
01:00:56.249 --> 01:00:59.729
He had to stay there,
to help her out.


271
01:00:59.809 --> 01:01:05.570
- Stayed? For how long?
- I don't know. A week or so, he said.


272
01:01:05.930 --> 01:01:09.090
- For that long?
- Mom, he will be back. Come on.


273
01:01:09.169 --> 01:01:14.209
- Are you hungry?
- No. I'm tired.


274
01:01:14.530 --> 01:01:16.249
Go rest, son.

275
01:01:16.809 --> 01:01:18.809
What's wrong my love?

276
01:01:19.370 --> 01:01:21.129
Nothing.

277
01:01:23.530 --> 01:01:25.890
- Just tired.
- Go finally rest.


278
01:02:50.649 --> 01:02:53.209
- I've missed you so much.
- Me too.


279
01:03:13.289 --> 01:03:14.970
I'm tired.

280
01:03:16.530 --> 01:03:19.410
Tired? Ok.

281
01:03:24.930 --> 01:03:26.850
Let's do it tomorrow.

282
01:06:52.809 --> 01:06:54.649
I love you.

283
01:07:14.970 --> 01:07:18.289
SIBERIA AND HIM